The paper discusses a specific problem related to sparse matrix-vector multiplication and proposes a new data format that is optimized for modern processors with wide SIMD units. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories, including Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC), Architecture (cs.AR), Mathematical Software (cs.MS), Numerical Analysis (cs.NA), and Software Engineering (cs.SE). However, given the focus on hardware-specific optimization and performance analysis, we believe that cs.DC and cs.AR are the most likely sub-categories, followed by cs.MS, cs.NA, and cs.SE.
